<h2 id="why-did-wtc-need-an-ml-solution">Why did WTC need an ML solution?</h2>

<p>WTC was intended to help people identify mysterious charges on their credit card statements. But they didn‚Äôt know what the charges were either ‚Äì hence the idea for the business in the first place! So they designed WTC as a forum for user-generated content (UGC): the website would crowdsource the answers.</p>

<p>WTC‚Äôs UGC takes one of two forms.</p>

<p>Users submit a list of charges. But, sometimes users submit non-charges.
Users help to describe charges that have already been submitted. Each charge generates a page, and other people can then comment on it to explain what it is and how they know.</p>

<p>Both these forms of user submission were vulnerable to spam, hate speech, and so on ‚Äì as is typical of any UGC. Furthermore, a significant number of user comments were unhelpful for the site‚Äôs main function, such as venting about the frustration of not knowing what a charge is ‚Äì not helpful when you‚Äôre simply trying to find a quick answer.</p>

<p>So, WTC needed to manually moderate this content, classifying user-submitted charges as ‚Äúis a charge‚Äù or ‚Äúis not a charge‚Äù, and user-submitted descriptions as ‚Äúhelpful‚Äù or ‚Äúnot helpful‚Äù. They even had cases of people typing in their credit card details and asking WTC for a refund, which needed to be removed quickly to prevent fraud.</p>

<p>Jeremy realized that ML had advanced a lot since the inception of the company, and that they should be able to use ML to classify user submissions automatically.</p>

<div class="customer-quote-block" style="padding-left:5%;padding-right:15%">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-8">
            <div class="customer-quote p-10">"There wasn‚Äôt an API in the world that tells you if something‚Äôs a charge or not. It‚Äôs too niche. Nothing else \[apart from ML] could moderate that."</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 pl-0">
            <div class="customer-quote-signature">
                
                <picture style="display: inline-block;">
                    <img src="https://www.nyckel.com/_content/Marketing/images/mugshot-wtc.jpg" class="case-study-mugshot" loading="lazy" alt="" style="max-width: 100%;" />
                </picture>
                

                <div class="p-l-15">
                    <div class="customer-quote-name">Jeremy Schneider</div>
                    <div class="customer-quote-title">Co-founder, WTC</div>
